# Development Workflow

## Branch Strategy

| Branch Type | Prefix | Purpose |
|-------------|--------|---------|
| Feature | `feature/` | New functionality |
| Bug Fix | `fix/` | Bug repairs |
| Tech Debt | `refactor/task-N-` | Code improvements |

## Workflow Steps

### 1. Create Branch

```bash
git checkout main && git pull
git checkout -b <prefix>/<description>
```

### 2. Implement Changes

- Follow coding standards
- Update documentation
- Add/update tests

### 3. Quality Checks

{{#if frontend}}
**Frontend**:
```bash
cd {{FRONTEND_DIR}}
{{FRONTEND_LINT_CMD}}
```
{{/if}}

{{#if backend}}
**Backend**:
```bash
cd {{BACKEND_DIR}}
{{BACKEND_FORMAT_CMD}}
```
{{/if}}

### 4. Verification

{{#if docker}}
```bash
cd {{DOCKER_DIR}}
docker compose up -d --build
```
{{else}}
Run all services locally and verify functionality.
{{/if}}

### 5. Create PR

{{#if github}}
```bash
gh pr create --title "<type>: <description>" --body "..."
```
{{else}}
Create PR/MR in your git platform.
{{/if}}

### 6. Review & Merge

- Wait for CI to pass
- Get user/team approval
- Squash merge to main

## Commit Message Format

```
